# TryHackMe - W1seGuy

## Room
https://tryhackme.com/room/w1seguy

## Category
Cryptography

## Difficulty
Easy

## Description
W1seGuy is a cryptography challenge based on XOR encryption and a known plaintext attack.

## Concepts Learned

- XOR encryptions
- Known plaintext attacks
- Key recovery
- Brute forcing XOR keys
- Python scripting

## Approach

The challenge provides an XOR encrypted ciphertext. Since the flag format starts with:
THM{

  
After recovering the partial key, the remaining character was brute-forced to obtain the complete XOR key and decrypt the flag.

## Tools Used

- Netcat
- Python
- CyberChef

## Solution

The XOR key was recovered by exploiting the known plaintext (`THM{`) and then used to decrypt the complete ciphertext.

THM{p1alntExtAtt4ckcAnr3alLyhUrty0urxOr

    
## Takeaways

This challenge demonstrated why using simple XOR encryption with a repeating key is insecure when part of the plaintext is known.
